description:
English translation of the Japanese manga Ajin (亜人).

SAY YOU GET HIT BY A TRUCK AND DIE. YOU COME BACK TO LIFE. GOOD OR BAD?

For high schooler Kei -and for at least forty-six others- immortality comes as the nastiest surprise ever.

Sadly for Kei, but refreshingly for the reader, such a feat doesn’t make him a superhero. In the eyes of both the general public and governments, he’s a rare specimen who needs to be hunted down and handed over to scientists to be experimented on for life-a demi-human who must die a thousand deaths for the benefit of humanity.

Smart, fast-paced, and wrenching, Ajin: Demi-Human is a thriller that just keeps on getting better and deeper.
name: Ajin: Demi-Human

description:
English translation of the Japanese manga Mahō Shōjo of the End (魔法少女・オブ・ジ・エンド).

The zombie survival genre has just met its match! High-schooler Kii Kogami is stuck in a rut, loathing the monotonous doldrums of his everyday life. If only something exciting were to happen, something magical. As fate would have it, Kii is about to get his wish, but in a way more terrifying than anything he could have imagined. When a little girl clad in gothic lolita attire appears at school and starts to gruesomely bludgeon, dismember and mutilate all who cross her path, while chanting the mantra 'Magical Girl' under her breath, the school devolves into a state of bloody chaos. Just how will Kii escape from this murderous magical girl?
name: Magical Girl Apocalypse

deck: A few hours ago, they weren't sentient. But now this quartet of single-celled amoebas is ready to utilize their weaponry and fight the evil Mem-Brain and his hordes of plasmodia and paramecia!
description:
In a world spanning a single drop of water, trouble from the likes of the evil Mem-Brain and his hordes of Plasmodium soldiers threatens peaceful paramecia everywhere. Fortunately, there is hope! The Astounding Amoeba Armada may add up to a total of four cells, but size isn't everything. Amoebas on a mission, this quartet is trained to kick some major butt - and they don't even have butts.

Trained by the mysterious Poly-Chaos, Cyc, Beanpole, Lil, and Tubes are ready, willing, and able to send Mem-Brain right out the water drop once and for all. This quartet isn't just trained to use mystical weapons, they are their weapons.
name: The Astounding Amoeba Armada
